---
/**
 * storage-engines · storage-engines-fundamentals · Figure 2 — Level 1, the
 * append-only log + in-RAM hash index (Bitcask).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source page (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). The source declared its arrowhead markers ONCE in a hidden
 * top-of-body <svg defs>; this figure references marker-end="url(#arwG)", so the
 * green #arwG marker is inlined here in a local <defs> (verbatim from the source
 * defs block) so it resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 170"
        role="img"
        aria-label="An append-only log on disk with an in-memory hash index; reads follow the index to an offset, writes append and repoint"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="14" y="14" width="240" height="40" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="134"
                y="32"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">IN-RAM hash index</text
            >
            <text x="134" y="47" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >key → byte offset</text
            >
            <g font-size="9" fill="#111110">
                <text x="30" y="78">foo → 96</text><text x="30" y="94">bar → 32</text>
            </g>
            <text
                x="400"
                y="14"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">APPEND-ONLY log on disk</text
            >
            <g font-size="9.5">
                <rect x="290" y="24" width="78" height="26" rx="5" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect><text x="329" y="41" text-anchor="middle">bar,9</text>
                <rect x="372" y="24" width="78" height="26" rx="5" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect><text x="411" y="41" text-anchor="middle">foo,1</text>
                <rect x="454" y="24" width="92" height="26" rx="5" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect><text x="500" y="41" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7a1f12" font-weight="700"
                    >foo,42 ←tail</text
                >
            </g>
            <!-- read arrow -->
            <path
                d="M 90 70 C 200 110, 420 90, 480 52"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"
                marker-end="url(#arwG)"></path>
            <text x="300" y="120" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >READ: hash lookup (O(1)) → 1 seek to offset → 1 record</text
            >
            <!-- write arrow -->
            <path d="M 540 58 C 545 96, 545 96, 540 96" fill="none" stroke="#7a1f12"></path>
            <text x="300" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a1f12"
                >WRITE: append 1 record at the tail + repoint 1 map entry</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#9a2417"
                >✗ keyset must fit in RAM&#160;&#160;✗ no range queries</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Bitcask (Riak's engine): append the data, keep <code>key → offset</code> in RAM. Reads do one
        lookup + one seek regardless of file size.<sup><a href="#s6" id="r6">6</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
